Renewable energy development movement

Since the progress in renewable energy development is driven mainly by rationalizing the industrial structure, this is of utmost importance. Progress in industrialization, as a regressor, has a marginally insignificant direct influence, a substantial indirect effect, and a substantial overall effect on the slowdown in environmentally friendly growth. On the one hand, manufacturing sector development usually involves upgrading from a previous stage in the sector’s structure. From a scientific viewpoint, the pollution issues that arise when the primary industry is transformed into industrialization on the way to the advanced level are mitigated once the tremendously changed to the tertiary transition stage. Therefore, when the industrial structure evolves into a more sophisticated form, there should be a U-shaped shift in the degree of sustainable innovation (Table 7). However, the focus of China’s present growth is still on the country’s traditional sectors.Table 7
